WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:38.540
﻿Šime, good afternoon.

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:44.761
I am grateful that you came
to our show and decided

00:00:45.324 --> 00:00:50.420
to share some tidbits
from your rich career with us.

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:55.660
You recently said
goodbye to football,

00:00:55.770 --> 00:00:58.410
and my first question is,
how are you? How is your health?

00:00:58.564 --> 00:01:00.884
And what condition
is your body in?

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:06.140
Good afternoon, it's a great
pleasure for me to be here

00:01:06.500 --> 00:01:11.700
and talk about football
and my personal life,

00:01:12.100 --> 00:01:15.100
during my career
and after it.

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:21.700
I can only say
everything is different now.

00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:26.100
For many years, sports came
first, but now after my career,

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:29.980
I have more time
for other things.

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:34.460
I have a lot to say,
but in general, I am satisfied.

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:39.020
Following the media, I noticed
that you've started working as a manager.

00:01:39.260 --> 00:01:41.460
Is that true, or is it
only partially true?

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:44.180
Tell us more about it.

00:01:44.460 --> 00:01:48.420
I have a strong desire
to pursue that career

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:51.820
and become a football agent.
I want to stay connected

00:01:52.100 --> 00:01:55.420
to those players and progress,
as it's something new.

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:00.100
It's a process that needs
to start from scratch,

00:02:00.238 --> 00:02:02.530
to be learned and improved upon.

00:02:02.695 --> 00:02:04.895
It's not unfamiliar to me
since, when I started

00:02:05.113 --> 00:02:07.353
playing football, I also
started from zero.

00:02:07.674 --> 00:02:10.905
However, the great experience
I've gained throughout my career

00:02:11.076 --> 00:02:14.180
gives me the confidence
to sit on the other side of the table

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:17.900
and be competent
in this role as well.

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:23.029
I am aware that it takes time,
and we, former athletes,

00:02:23.584 --> 00:02:28.399
myself included,
need to educate ourselves.

00:02:28.892 --> 00:02:33.121
That's what I'm striving for,
but I'm not rushing.

00:02:33.228 --> 00:02:34.960
I’m taking it step by step.

00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:40.220
Let’s go back to the beginning:
your childhood, your early years.

00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:47.500
When I found out you were born
in my town, Rijeka,

00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:51.420
it surprised me. You later
explained it was due

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:56.141
to certain circumstances.
Tell us more about your early childhood

00:02:56.273 --> 00:02:58.593
and your memories
of Zadar and the sea.

00:02:58.755 --> 00:03:01.395
Those were difficult times,
it was during the war.

00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:05.620
Tell us more about that.
-It was nice.

00:03:10.260 --> 00:03:14.340
My mother gave birth to me
in Rijeka during the war.

00:03:14.660 --> 00:03:19.020
We had some relatives in Zadar,
and my mother gave birth to me there

00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:21.980
because that’s what
my parents decided.

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:27.460
That’s why my documents say
I was born in Rijeka.

00:03:27.614 --> 00:03:31.793
People often associate me with Rijeka,
but there’s nothing more

00:03:32.339 --> 00:03:34.997
to it than just
being born there.

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:47.788
After that, I grew up in Zadar,
like any Dalmatian boy who felt called

00:03:48.418 --> 00:03:52.618
to sports, particularly to football.

00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:59.780
Football was inevitable
for me; it was my everyday life,

00:04:00.062 --> 00:04:02.924
playing in the streets,
which isn’t so common anymore.

00:04:03.118 --> 00:04:06.549
Today, fewer and fewer children
play outside. They’re more...

00:04:06.628 --> 00:04:08.628
We all play video games.

00:04:09.005 --> 00:04:13.877
Exactly. I’m happy
that I had that experience,

00:04:14.063 --> 00:04:21.151
although it didn’t last long.
After I started playing football at seven,

00:04:26.088 --> 00:04:32.020
there was less and less time
for those typical childhood activities.

00:04:32.398 --> 00:04:36.355
Some of those boyish pastimes
and a normal way of life faded.

00:04:36.635 --> 00:04:40.597
When I was my peers’ age,
football didn’t allow me

00:04:40.742 --> 00:04:44.167
to do that. However,
I wasn’t burdened by it at the time

00:04:45.108 --> 00:04:48.228
because football was the most
important thing to me.

00:04:48.773 --> 00:04:50.940
It made me happy.

00:04:51.229 --> 00:04:58.136
It wasn’t hard for me to sacrifice
so many things other boys my age enjoyed

00:04:58.290 --> 00:05:01.362
because football was
what made me the happiest.

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:06.180
Tell me, how did you, growing up
in Zadar, a city known for basketball,

00:05:06.460 --> 00:05:14.544
decide to play football?
I also heard you played handball.

00:05:14.682 --> 00:05:17.082
Is that true?
-Yes, it’s true.

00:05:20.460 --> 00:05:28.820
When I was in elementary school,
my PE teacher organized a team

00:05:29.460 --> 00:05:34.740
to represent the school
in a city competition.

00:05:35.300 --> 00:05:41.900
I played for my school at that time
on the left wing. -Left wing?

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:48.260
Yes, considering I’m right-handed,
I played in the same position as you.

00:05:49.137 --> 00:05:53.930
I want to thank you for choosing
a different sport; it’s better that way.

00:05:54.220 --> 00:05:59.520
It was a phenomenal experience.
Speaking of handball, I must mention

00:05:59.758 --> 00:06:03.020
that I was a huge fan
of the Croatian handball national team,

00:06:03.282 --> 00:06:07.567
which you were a part of.
That was also a big part

00:06:07.775 --> 00:06:10.114
of my childhood
and growing up.

00:06:10.379 --> 00:06:14.459
It brings out a lot of emotions
and is ultimately connected

00:06:14.681 --> 00:06:18.011
to my career
in the national football team.

00:06:18.308 --> 00:06:22.903
Every sport that represented
our homeland gave us all a spark,

00:06:23.099 --> 00:06:27.700
and for those of us who grew up
in football and basketball,

00:06:27.896 --> 00:06:31.841
we were able to carry
that emotion forward.

00:06:32.202 --> 00:06:35.263
Energy is constantly moving,
it never goes away.

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:44.220
When did you realize
you were a good player?

00:06:44.540 --> 00:06:51.060
You had to realize that at some point.
It certainly didn't happen at an early age.

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:58.100
But when you were 13 or 14 years old,
Dinamo and Hajduk were interested in you.

00:06:58.340 --> 00:07:00.700
You must have been talented.

00:07:00.940 --> 00:07:06.180
During my time at the football club
Zadar and performances after that,

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:10.860
at the age of 13, I was a guest at two
tournaments while playing for Hajduk.

00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:13.620
I played on the right wing.

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:23.340
In that Darko Mateš tournament
at the Dragovoljac field,

00:07:24.180 --> 00:07:26.140
I was the best player.

00:07:26.420 --> 00:07:30.860
After that, we went to Osijek,
where we also won first place.

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:36.500
I saw myself then as a Hajduk player.

00:07:36.740 --> 00:07:41.175
For me, it was something special
to put on the jersey and listen

00:07:41.412 --> 00:07:46.496
to the fans' songs on the bus.

00:07:50.871 --> 00:07:56.791
It was something special for me.
However, then there was a twist.

00:07:57.068 --> 00:08:00.193
How did it happen that at one point
you were supposed to play for Hajduk,

00:08:00.320 --> 00:08:02.271
and after three days
you went to Dinamo?

00:08:02.580 --> 00:08:05.980
I don't want to talk about the names.
-We will not mention names.

00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:10.380
But the first information I received
from my father was:

00:08:10.980 --> 00:08:14.340
"Son, Hajduk is off."

00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:20.220
I played in two tournaments
and even packed up in the evening.

00:08:20.384 --> 00:08:24.456
My father and I packed our things
and said we would come in the morning.

00:08:24.612 --> 00:08:26.812
I came to the stadium
to become a Hajduk player.

00:08:26.998 --> 00:08:30.838
However, that evening, Hajduk
played a European match.

00:08:32.940 --> 00:08:38.220
I remember my father
telling me there was none of that.

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:45.740
He was giving me as much information
as he felt I was ready to accept.

00:08:45.926 --> 00:08:51.639
How do you tell a 14-year-old boy
from Dalmatia: "You are not going"?

00:08:57.300 --> 00:08:59.140
Okay, let's move on.

00:08:59.500 --> 00:09:03.100
From Zadar, a small town by the sea,
you moved to Zagreb.

00:09:03.340 --> 00:09:06.380
What were your first
experiences in Zagreb like?

00:09:06.550 --> 00:09:08.470
What was it like to come to Zagreb?

00:09:08.607 --> 00:09:12.407
I went to Zagreb with the goal
that I would succeed there

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:14.560
and that I could do it.

00:09:14.862 --> 00:09:19.826
However, at 14 years old,
I was not aware of everything

00:09:19.983 --> 00:09:21.928
that was about to happen.

00:09:22.032 --> 00:09:24.506
And the weight of it all.
-Maybe it's better that way.

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:28.500
Yes, it's better. We were
in the dorm at Maksimir.

00:09:30.420 --> 00:09:34.500
All the players from the club
used to go there because

00:09:34.686 --> 00:09:37.926
it was the dormitory where we lived.

00:09:38.110 --> 00:09:44.870
I spent six months there, and I really
can't complain that anything was wrong.

00:09:45.180 --> 00:09:51.540
I remember joking
about how we were doing.

00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:56.020
I actually wanted to say
how hard it was for me.

00:09:56.300 --> 00:10:01.300
I didn't want to say anything bad about
the dorm where I stayed for six months.

00:10:01.519 --> 00:10:03.839
On the contrary,
I think the best of it.

00:10:03.955 --> 00:10:06.425
I think it was a beautiful experience,
as difficult as it was.

00:10:06.643 --> 00:10:09.761
I have a billion anecdotes to tell you.

00:10:10.224 --> 00:10:16.152
Five or six of us slept in a room,
and the regime was like in the army.

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:26.237
In the dorm? -Every morning
we got up at 07:25, 07:20 or 07:30,

00:10:26.534 --> 00:10:28.894
I don't remember exactly.

00:10:30.260 --> 00:10:33.580
Of the six or five of us
who were in the room,

00:10:33.860 --> 00:10:35.980
the number always varied.

00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:41.300
every week, one of us was in charge
of cleaning everyone's rooms.

00:10:41.580 --> 00:10:45.620
You did it for seven days a week.

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:50.140
Every room, every section
had a teacher who came

00:10:50.340 --> 00:10:53.380
and checked how we did it.

00:10:54.700 --> 00:10:58.220
So, Šime Vrsaljko cleans on
such and such a date.

00:10:58.460 --> 00:11:03.140
I would get up in the morning,
make the beds, put things away.

00:11:03.540 --> 00:11:06.060
Then the teacher would
come in and evaluate me.

00:11:06.190 --> 00:11:08.430
It lasted for about six months.

00:11:08.569 --> 00:11:11.329
And then you moved
to private accommodation,

00:11:11.467 --> 00:11:14.827
where everything
seemed more normal.

00:11:14.961 --> 00:11:17.547
Yes, I moved quite a few times.
Five or six times.

00:11:17.703 --> 00:11:21.156
Is it because of unpaid bills or...?
-No, God forbid.

00:11:21.393 --> 00:11:23.833
Or did you not like the apartment?
-No, God forbid.

00:11:24.057 --> 00:11:29.734
Every one of those properties
where I lived during that time,

00:11:29.940 --> 00:11:33.180
until I was 18 or 19 years old,

00:11:33.367 --> 00:11:38.807
has its own story that is dear to
my heart and that I will never forget.

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:45.500
That certainly helped you while growing
up because, I assume, that was during

00:11:45.820 --> 00:11:51.700
the start of your career when your
financial situation wasn't the best.

00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:59.060
It must have been tough. -That was all
part of the process I had to go through.

00:11:59.940 --> 00:12:11.860
I think kids who leave home so early on
in their lives must grow up much faster.

00:12:12.540 --> 00:12:17.100
That happened to me. It's not easy.
Growing up in the blink of an eye

00:12:17.380 --> 00:12:23.020
doesn't mean that everything just gets
sorted out. It means you will go through

00:12:23.199 --> 00:12:27.359
many stressful situations and must learn
very quickly. Amongst those situations

00:12:27.577 --> 00:12:29.817
are also some bad influences.
After everything,

00:12:29.932 --> 00:12:32.652
you get a nice makeover that prepares
you for everything else coming your way.

00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:39.460
You were in the younger categories for
about 5 to 6 years while simultaneously

00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:43.540
being in the national teams
for them, right?

00:12:43.860 --> 00:12:47.300
It took you a long time
to get to the first team, right?

00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:54.340
It took you about 5 to 6 years... -Five.
-You debuted at 18 or 19 years old.

00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:58.740
At 17 years... -What was that
period like? Those five years?

00:12:58.940 --> 00:13:02.340
Did you start doubting yourself?
-Yes. -Yes? -Yes.

00:13:02.700 --> 00:13:08.500
I practically discovered that I was the
right-back when I was 17,5 years old.

00:13:09.220 --> 00:13:15.820
You just discovered your position then.
-When I was 14, 15, 16 years old...

00:13:16.100 --> 00:13:18.900
You were wandering...
-...I was playing cadet football.

00:13:19.180 --> 00:13:23.940
I was a defensive midfielder,
stopper, and right-wing.

00:13:24.460 --> 00:13:28.820
I was on the national team
as a left-back. At one point,

00:13:29.070 --> 00:13:34.227
I was in a situation where I would be
playing as a defensive midfielder,

00:13:34.510 --> 00:13:38.407
and people would say that
I wasn't the best at it

00:13:38.662 --> 00:13:43.743
and that I didn't have the talent
I was presenting to everyone.

00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:46.940
I felt that truly.

00:13:47.220 --> 00:13:49.940
Those people were far from being wrong
when we look at my performances.

00:13:50.180 --> 00:13:53.740
I reached my maximum but
learned a lot from every position.

00:13:54.020 --> 00:13:59.300
However, when I was younger, I already
played for the under-19 national team,

00:13:59.580 --> 00:14:05.168
where, for the first time, I felt what
it was like to play a back position

00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:11.260
and get a sense
of what I wanted. -Yes.

00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:18.621
At the time, Mr. Ivan Gudelj put me in
as a left-back because I would play

00:14:18.801 --> 00:14:21.740
with players up to 2 years
older than me when I was younger.

00:14:22.020 --> 00:14:26.860
At that time, they lacked this position,
and he said: "You are coming back here."

00:14:27.140 --> 00:14:32.978
I liked it, I felt free, I was good at it.
However, I returned to the club

00:14:33.337 --> 00:14:37.032
to play in my old position
and felt something was off.

00:14:37.829 --> 00:14:43.340
That was going on until... Meanwhile,
I signed a contract with Dinamo.

00:14:43.660 --> 00:14:53.370
I was about 17,5 or 18 years old when I
had a professional contract with Dinamo,

00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:58.260
but I wondered what my next step was.

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:08.794
Thank god I had my parents,
my gut feeling,

00:15:10.059 --> 00:15:18.712
the man who, alongside my coach,
brought me to Dinamo, Božidar Šekić,

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:26.425
and Jozo Bandić by my side.
He was my coach for a long time

00:15:27.417 --> 00:15:36.580
and helped shape me as a person
and player. To get back to Božidar,

00:15:37.380 --> 00:15:43.660
he was president of the club Lokomotiva
and the man who brought me to Dinamo.

00:15:43.940 --> 00:15:48.760
When I was 17,5 years old, while
Lokomotiva was playing their first

00:15:50.823 --> 00:15:58.070
Croatian League, he asked me if I would
come in as a loan player for a year.

00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:01.132
And I said I would do it.
-Without thinking it through? -Yes.

00:16:01.316 --> 00:16:04.327
From Dinamo...  -Yes.
-From a better club to a worse one?

00:16:04.541 --> 00:16:08.101
I wasn't going to join the first team
for Dinamo... - Listen to this, kids!

00:16:08.940 --> 00:16:15.222
I went to club Lokomotiva. If it
wasn't for that team, for Lokomotiva,

00:16:19.852 --> 00:16:26.420
I think my career would go in
a completely different direction.

00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:30.180
Really? Do you think
it was that important?

00:16:30.420 --> 00:16:37.180
The team captain at the time, currently
the coach of the football club Rijeka,

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:45.060
Željko Sopić, alongside Nino Bule,
were already tough players

00:16:45.380 --> 00:16:50.336
and were helping us younger players.
That's just how things were.

00:16:50.641 --> 00:16:56.700
I came in as a defensive midfielder.
-And Sopić was playing that position?

00:16:56.871 --> 00:16:59.311
Sopić was playing that position, etc.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:07.820
That existing structure was small
but united, and Roy Ferenčina,

00:17:09.759 --> 00:17:15.266
the current Slaven Belupo football club
coach, was a part of it.

00:17:15.683 --> 00:17:22.932
After approximately ten practices, after
talking with Bule, Željko, and Božidar,

00:17:23.258 --> 00:17:30.538
the Lokomotiva football club coach
who approved this, Roy Ferenčina said:

00:17:30.940 --> 00:17:33.580
"We will put him as a right-back."

00:17:33.766 --> 00:17:35.686
And that's it?
-That's how it started.

00:17:35.856 --> 00:17:37.976
And that's how you returned
to Dinamo as a right-back?

00:17:38.161 --> 00:17:41.201
That is when my career as a right-back
started. Up until that point,

00:17:41.427 --> 00:17:45.747
nobody ever put me in that position.
I felt left-back position calling me.

00:17:45.863 --> 00:17:48.943
I always wondered what it would be like
if I played on the right,

00:17:49.144 --> 00:17:52.792
where my dominant leg was naturally
moving. -Yes. -I was managing just fine.

00:17:53.291 --> 00:17:57.863
If it wasn't for Lokomotiva
and those six months of playing,

00:17:58.374 --> 00:18:02.094
and if it wasn't for that ambient
and those wonderful people

00:18:02.263 --> 00:18:06.583
who recognized that, then Dinamo
would not have taken me back.

00:18:06.752 --> 00:18:12.672
No what-ifs... What I truly felt
at that moment was that I could only be

00:18:12.998 --> 00:18:18.566
beneficial to the team in that position.
Everything I achieved in that position

00:18:19.019 --> 00:18:25.546
later on was thanks to the Lokomotiva
football club, which gave me a chance.

00:18:31.100 --> 00:18:34.380
Do you remember your debut
in HNL? What was it like?

00:18:34.620 --> 00:18:39.380
I remember...
It wasn't very pleasant.

00:18:40.460 --> 00:18:50.860
I remember even having cramps. It was
all psychologically stressful for me.

00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:57.500
That year, you got your first title.
Is that right? Croatian Championship.

00:18:58.100 --> 00:19:02.220
Your first title. You won... -Four.
-Dinamo was untouchable back then.

00:19:02.464 --> 00:19:06.544
You won four titles. What was
the feeling for that first title?

00:19:06.752 --> 00:19:12.232
Was there a celebration in Zagreb,
or was that just something normal for you?

00:19:12.386 --> 00:19:15.146
How do you remember
that first championship?

00:19:15.339 --> 00:19:17.819
Or maybe that was considered
something normal at that time...

00:19:18.071 --> 00:19:27.462
Yes, it was a mix... It wasn't that
unusual in Zagreb to win championships

00:19:27.620 --> 00:19:31.300
with such a huge point difference...

00:19:31.536 --> 00:19:38.243
However, that was remarkable for me as
a child and a young man at that moment.

00:19:38.700 --> 00:19:45.780
During that year, Kruno Jurčić was
the coach, and then Vahid Halilhodžić

00:19:46.140 --> 00:19:49.260
came the following year. We all know
about the fallout with Zdravko

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:54.580
and how that ended... However,
I am interested in Halilhodžić

00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:59.220
and his way of coaching. I heard
that he is a particular, unique coach.

00:19:59.396 --> 00:20:02.476
How did that look like
from your perspective?

00:20:02.645 --> 00:20:06.805
That was the first non-Croatian
coach that you came across...

00:20:06.904 --> 00:20:09.722
You took the words out of my mouth.
-How did that look?

00:20:09.947 --> 00:20:13.746
How do you remember those days?
From this perspective...

00:20:14.580 --> 00:20:25.540
It was hard. Mr. Vahid Halilhodžić
is a coach of European caliber.

00:20:25.980 --> 00:20:30.660
He is a coach who, when you
look at his contributions,

00:20:30.940 --> 00:20:34.380
had his results as proof of his
abilities even after Dinamo.

00:20:34.660 --> 00:20:45.220
When he came for the first time,
without undermining Krunoslav Jurčić,

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:51.300
who was a phenomenal coach...
I can freely say that he was a coach

00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:56.340
with abundant knowledge
from whom I learned a lot.

00:20:56.455 --> 00:20:59.432
However, as it goes in football,
the results weren't good,

00:20:59.515 --> 00:21:01.435
so the coach changed.
-Classic...

00:21:03.660 --> 00:21:07.140
That year, we also played
the European Championship.

00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:11.180
We prepared in a completely
different way for those games.

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:15.540
The new coach had a very different
character from the previous one.

00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:23.100
He was much tougher, and we weren't used
to that – coming from a 19-year-old me.

00:21:29.060 --> 00:21:33.340
We really enjoyed working with him.

00:21:33.700 --> 00:21:38.900
Despite how strict he was,
he was always fair in everything.

00:21:39.140 --> 00:21:43.940
He has a higher level
of professionalism,

00:21:44.260 --> 00:21:51.420
which he gained before joining Dinamo.
He translated that into his work with us

00:21:51.740 --> 00:21:56.820
when he became the coach
for the football club Dinamo.

00:21:59.460 --> 00:22:03.820
We were successful with him
and had many phenomenal moments.

00:22:04.140 --> 00:22:09.060
There was a lot of laughter then.
There was a time when, every day

00:22:09.340 --> 00:22:12.900
before practice, we would have to
stand in line, one by one, and shake

00:22:13.140 --> 00:22:17.100
the coach's and all of his
assistant's hands.-All lined up?

00:22:17.380 --> 00:22:20.820
Exactly, all lined up,
one by one, shaking his hand.

00:22:21.060 --> 00:22:24.286
Good afternoon, coach. Good afternoon.
-There were times when he didn't know

00:22:24.452 --> 00:22:26.612
a particular word
and would say it in French.

00:22:26.774 --> 00:22:29.955
Sometimes, he would do it intentionally
when he saw that it made us laugh.

00:22:30.089 --> 00:22:32.821
He would do it intentionally
to brighten up the mood.

00:22:32.945 --> 00:22:37.130
I personally felt terrible when he left.

00:22:38.300 --> 00:22:44.700
That year, you won
with a 17-point difference.

00:22:45.300 --> 00:22:51.140
Looking back now, do you think
it was an advantage or a disadvantage

00:22:51.380 --> 00:22:56.580
that Dinamo was so dominant at the time,
and it was almost a given that they

00:22:56.940 --> 00:23:02.940
would win the championship?
They were overwhelmingly dominant.

00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:08.780
Compared to today's situation,
now we have Rijeka, Hajduk, and Dinamo,

00:23:09.020 --> 00:23:11.940
making it a much healthier situation
from a sporting perspective.

00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:16.380
What do you think from
this perspective?

00:23:16.620 --> 00:23:20.140
For me and for my career,
for the position I played at,

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:23.940
besides the matches
and the experience in Europe,

00:23:24.980 --> 00:23:27.940
which during Vahid Halilhodžić's
period was phenomenal.

00:23:28.140 --> 00:23:30.780
We beat Villarreal at home, etc.

00:23:32.820 --> 00:23:36.180
We made an impression
as a serious European team.

00:23:36.420 --> 00:23:39.420
Practices were different,
and we were prepared.

00:23:39.620 --> 00:23:42.300
Everything was well-organized.
We felt secure.

00:23:42.540 --> 00:23:45.420
It was a mix of youth
and the experience of older players,

00:23:45.580 --> 00:23:48.220
so we looked the way we did.

00:23:48.660 --> 00:23:52.980
However, I can speak
for myself and for my career.

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:57.340
What I experienced with my first
move abroad, to Italy.

00:24:00.580 --> 00:24:04.540
The offensive football
we played at Dinamo,

00:24:11.420 --> 00:24:15.380
and my later position...
-You moved to right-back.

00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:21.580
Moving to the right-back position
and the short period I played there,

00:24:21.860 --> 00:24:29.565
through football, made me realize
how much I didn't know how to defend.

00:24:31.089 --> 00:24:37.958
Tactically I wasn't
at the level I thought I was.

00:24:39.201 --> 00:24:42.598
Next came Genoa.

00:24:43.580 --> 00:24:49.300
You're talking about the first impressions
in the top five leagues, Italy,

00:24:49.700 --> 00:24:52.820
the difference between
Croatian and Italian football.

00:24:53.020 --> 00:24:58.453
It's not about Croatian football, not to
underestimate the league at that time,

00:24:58.648 --> 00:25:02.708
but rather the club I played for.
Because of the way we played.

00:25:02.829 --> 00:25:04.965
It was offensive football.

00:25:05.473 --> 00:25:10.200
My tendency as a right-back
was that I liked to move forward.

00:25:10.632 --> 00:25:16.232
However, in one year we only
had a few games in the season

00:25:16.586 --> 00:25:19.346
where I was in a situation to defend,

00:25:19.780 --> 00:25:23.540
where I was being attacked,
It was all kind of...

00:25:26.260 --> 00:25:32.060
I would say maybe it was a bad
choice of club? -No.

00:25:32.380 --> 00:25:35.700
Coming from offensive Dinamo,
where you're always going

00:25:35.900 --> 00:25:38.340
towards the goal,
you come to Genoa where,

00:25:38.540 --> 00:25:41.180
against stronger clubs,
you have to defend.

00:25:41.700 --> 00:25:45.980
It wasn’t a bad choice.
For me, the choice was perfect.

00:25:46.220 --> 00:25:50.740
That only became clear later.
Why? Because in Italy

00:25:51.020 --> 00:25:56.420
I improved in defense,
and through my time in Genoa,

00:25:56.620 --> 00:25:59.900
and two years at Sassuolo where
I had a phenomenal coach.

00:26:00.100 --> 00:26:02.780
Many were skeptical
about my move to Sassuolo.

00:26:02.980 --> 00:26:06.420
You spent three years in Italy?
-Three. -One year at Genoa,

00:26:06.780 --> 00:26:09.140
and two at Sassuolo.
-That's right.

00:26:09.731 --> 00:26:15.810
First, learning defensive
movements on the pitch,

00:26:17.146 --> 00:26:22.357
playing every
weekend at that level...

00:26:23.768 --> 00:26:27.285
It becomes normal. - ...where you
can be threatened at any moment.

00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:31.740
That pushed me, as well
as the club and coaches,

00:26:32.020 --> 00:26:36.580
to show me things
I realized I didn’t know.

00:26:37.100 --> 00:26:40.380
I was used to just going forward.

00:26:40.700 --> 00:26:44.461
However, I came to a smaller club...
-You need to get back to defense too.

00:26:44.726 --> 00:26:48.891
...which mostly defends,
football was played differently.

00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:53.660
It was a nice experience
for me, but also difficult.

00:26:53.766 --> 00:26:56.049
And surprising. -Yes.
-To see where you are.

00:26:56.154 --> 00:26:58.114
I didn’t speak the language.

00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:02.073
There’s also the fear of failure,
the first impression I would leave

00:27:02.740 --> 00:27:12.797
as a player coming from a small country
and a weaker league compared to Serie A.

00:27:15.060 --> 00:27:18.260
I can say that I improved
a lot during that one year.

00:27:18.500 --> 00:27:27.340
It wasn’t easy. In that year,
Liverani was the coach.

00:27:27.580 --> 00:27:35.060
After him, Gasperini came,
who had a completely different system.

00:27:36.180 --> 00:27:41.060
I didn’t really get along with him.
-That was my next question.

00:27:41.300 --> 00:27:46.500
How did the move to Sassuolo
happen? Now you’ve answered it.

00:27:46.700 --> 00:27:50.340
People didn’t even know how to
pronounce the name of the club.

00:27:50.620 --> 00:27:54.620
I followed the idea that I should
go to a club where I would play,

00:27:54.860 --> 00:27:58.620
where I could keep improving...
-Playing time was key? -That’s right.

00:27:58.820 --> 00:28:03.900
You were the best right-back
in the league there.

00:28:04.312 --> 00:28:07.272
The best fullback in Serie A.

00:28:08.660 --> 00:28:14.496
Were you sixth or seventh then?
-We played in Europe. -Bravo.

00:28:19.980 --> 00:28:22.860
Then came the peak
of your career.

00:28:23.180 --> 00:28:29.860
How did the offer from
Atletico Madrid come about?

00:28:30.100 --> 00:28:34.523
I read that the sums were huge.

00:28:35.078 --> 00:28:40.046
I never imagined in my wildest dreams
that I would go to Spain. -Really? -No.

00:28:40.780 --> 00:28:43.300
If I were a footballer,
that would be my dream.

00:28:43.900 --> 00:28:48.580
When I was at Dinamo,
they always talked about England.

00:28:48.740 --> 00:28:50.900
Manchester, Arsenal.

00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:53.980
Which could have happened,
but didn’t materialize.

00:28:54.220 --> 00:28:59.100
Then Italy came out of nowhere.
-And England was in play? -Yes.

00:28:59.380 --> 00:29:02.420
At that time, I was focused
only on England.

00:29:02.660 --> 00:29:07.180
I was young, the newspapers
constantly wrote about me,

00:29:07.500 --> 00:29:10.380
I wasn’t ready for all that information
and everything that was happening.

00:29:10.620 --> 00:29:16.420
My desire at the time
was to go to Inter.

00:29:17.980 --> 00:29:22.940
That didn’t happen and I
ended up at Atletico Madrid.

00:29:23.180 --> 00:29:27.900
Not bad. -I don’t regret it,
but I never imagined myself there.

00:29:28.180 --> 00:29:30.340
When I arrived...

00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:38.420
How big was the difference?
Sassuolo - Atletico?

00:29:38.620 --> 00:29:41.860
In everything? -Huge.
-Let’s forget Madrid and Spain.

00:29:42.100 --> 00:29:48.345
The way the club operates.
-A huge difference.

00:29:49.700 --> 00:29:54.700
I had the privilege to play
the last year at Vicente Calderon.

00:29:55.300 --> 00:29:59.380
That was a great pleasure for me.
-Gave me goosebumps.

00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:05.580
That stadium has such history,
and so much emotion.

00:30:05.820 --> 00:30:10.060
I had the chance to be
there in its final year.

00:30:11.260 --> 00:30:15.900
It was a big change
in my career in terms of work,

00:30:16.180 --> 00:30:29.540
with a coach who accomplished
so much with Atletico Madrid.

00:30:30.500 --> 00:30:35.220
As a player as well. -And his
playing career. -In every sense.

00:30:35.460 --> 00:30:40.580
The way he worked and the staff he had.
I knew the training was intense.

00:30:40.820 --> 00:30:50.540
What is he like as a person?
-Diego is a unique personality.

00:30:52.780 --> 00:30:58.460
When I arrived, I felt,
I won’t say coldness,

00:30:59.660 --> 00:31:06.940
but I felt an energy that told me
I had to prove myself.

00:31:07.180 --> 00:31:10.300
Nowhere was the competition
like at Atletico Madrid.

00:31:10.540 --> 00:31:15.260
No club was at the level
of Atletico Madrid.

00:31:16.140 --> 00:31:19.460
The league I played in was
nowhere near the Spanish league.

00:31:19.700 --> 00:31:22.380
The clubs I faced
in the Spanish league,

00:31:22.620 --> 00:31:26.820
not to underestimate the clubs in Italy,
which was also a huge experience.

00:31:27.020 --> 00:31:31.220
A totally different concept of the
league itself and the way it’s played,

00:31:31.460 --> 00:31:34.780
and the specific style of play of
Atletico Madrid and Diego Simeone,

00:31:34.940 --> 00:31:37.407
his football is unique
in its own way.

00:31:40.340 --> 00:31:44.420
He set it up in his own way,
and it took time

00:31:44.620 --> 00:31:50.780
for me to adapt and accept everything.
That requires a lot of work, patience,

00:31:51.220 --> 00:31:54.833
and a strong mind. Why?
For the first time in my life,

00:31:55.084 --> 00:31:57.324
I’m encountering three
practices a day.

00:31:58.173 --> 00:32:01.153
During preparations?
-During preparations.

00:32:02.700 --> 00:32:11.300
In that period, for a week,
you have 2-3 practices.

00:32:12.335 --> 00:32:16.747
That means, when you
have two, it’s tough.

00:32:17.114 --> 00:32:22.434
Preparations are very demanding.
A completely different way of working.

00:32:23.204 --> 00:32:28.292
In terms of the gym, running,
tactics, and the pressure itself.

00:32:28.883 --> 00:32:34.443
The closeness when
performing any exercise.

00:32:35.241 --> 00:32:40.443
They are always present. -There is always
noise, pressure, and nervousness.

00:32:42.373 --> 00:32:46.420
It’s like a bomb full of energy
that can explode at any moment.

00:32:46.620 --> 00:32:50.260
It’s constant like that.
That’s the pressure

00:32:50.500 --> 00:32:53.540
that is consciously
or unconsciously created,

00:32:53.740 --> 00:32:57.943
but it forces you to always
be at this level.

00:32:58.150 --> 00:33:00.670
At every practice?
-That’s right.

00:33:02.580 --> 00:33:06.900
There were practices when there
was a bit of relaxation, but rarely.

00:33:07.420 --> 00:33:10.860
However, at that time, I was faced
with three training sessions a day,

00:33:11.140 --> 00:33:13.740
which means you wake up
at six in the morning.

00:33:14.020 --> 00:33:18.420
The first practice is at 7:25.
You go to the golf course.

00:33:18.980 --> 00:33:23.808
And you run. -You run there.
-That’s where the work happens.

00:33:25.180 --> 00:33:28.780
When that practice ends,
we go for breakfast.

00:33:29.100 --> 00:33:32.460
The second practice is
at 12:30 in the gym.

00:33:32.700 --> 00:33:34.540
And the third practice is
in the afternoon.

00:33:34.780 --> 00:33:39.460
Did he perhaps play handball
in his youth? -He might have.

00:33:41.140 --> 00:33:47.260
You had to adapt to all of that.

00:33:47.500 --> 00:33:56.900
Before my arrival at Atletico Madrid,
there always was play, play, play.

00:33:57.700 --> 00:34:01.860
At Atletico Madrid,
for the first time, I didn’t play.

00:34:03.100 --> 00:34:05.700
I couldn’t accept that.

00:34:06.340 --> 00:34:08.940
That’s a burden in your head,
and it’s tough.

00:34:09.220 --> 00:34:12.660
Angry, young and
inexperienced in many things.

00:34:12.860 --> 00:34:17.860
I won’t say impulsive, but simply
it was devastating for me.

00:34:18.060 --> 00:34:20.260
I won’t say there was injustice,

00:34:20.500 --> 00:34:25.060
I just fought for my
playing time as an athlete.

00:34:25.191 --> 00:34:27.151
I’ll tell you an anecdote.

00:34:30.180 --> 00:34:34.860
I didn't play in the first two or
three games of the championship.

00:34:35.580 --> 00:34:38.100
You weren't in the lineup at all?
Not even on the bench?

00:34:38.340 --> 00:34:40.060
I was on the stands.

00:34:40.660 --> 00:34:43.140
That first year when you came?
-That's right.

00:34:43.380 --> 00:34:46.101
The first game I was on the stands.

00:34:46.306 --> 00:34:50.117
I was on the bench for the second game.
Played the third in the first 11.

00:34:50.324 --> 00:34:52.644
And then I go to the stands again...

00:34:55.060 --> 00:34:57.860
Then I went to talk to him.

00:34:59.220 --> 00:35:03.882
I said, "Boss, it's hard for me
to play like that...

00:35:04.157 --> 00:35:07.517
Stands, then bench, then I play.

00:35:08.031 --> 00:35:12.311
It was difficult to adapt to it
and catch the rhythm...

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:17.420
Catch up with your
teammates at that moment

00:35:17.660 --> 00:35:21.020
to feel like a part of
the game completely.

00:35:22.660 --> 00:35:29.020
And he tells me: "It is possible
that you will be in the stands

00:35:29.260 --> 00:35:34.100
for the next match, but after
that you will be in the first eleven.

00:35:34.420 --> 00:35:38.860
Because, from the stands,
you can better see how we play.

00:35:40.100 --> 00:35:42.100
That was the explanation?

00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:46.740
That's right. So, from the stands
I can see player movements better.

00:35:46.980 --> 00:35:50.980
So I got an answer
that I didn't expect at all.

00:35:52.460 --> 00:35:57.180
I looked at him and said,
"Okay, I accept any decision."

00:35:57.341 --> 00:35:59.541
Was he joking with you
or did he really mean it?

00:35:59.733 --> 00:36:01.733
I believe he really thought so.

00:36:02.020 --> 00:36:05.380
And looking back now,
I think it makes sense,

00:36:05.620 --> 00:36:08.740
because when you are up
in the stands, and if you follow,

00:36:08.980 --> 00:36:12.196
you can see the movements better.
You can see each position better.

00:36:12.360 --> 00:36:14.480
I'm new, I just came...
-It's a better perspective.

00:36:14.674 --> 00:36:17.634
I'm young, I need time to
catch the rhythm and so on.

00:36:17.904 --> 00:36:25.667
However, after that period
of 6 months of training and playing...

00:36:26.380 --> 00:36:31.700
Of adjustment... -Yes,
and my struggles for position,

00:36:31.980 --> 00:36:36.820
I finally succeeded. But there was also
screaming and crying at practices,

00:36:37.020 --> 00:36:41.500
all kinds of things. However,
it was strictly professional.

00:36:41.655 --> 00:36:45.420
I accepted that and decided
to fight for my position.

00:36:51.060 --> 00:36:54.340
Eventually, when I started
playing regularly

00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:57.380
he remembered that
he could trust me.

00:36:57.620 --> 00:37:00.300
That happened in the first season?
-Yes, that's right.

00:37:02.740 --> 00:37:05.620
It was the end of the 12th month,
the beginning of the first

00:37:05.900 --> 00:37:09.700
or something like that.
He trusted me more and more.

00:37:10.580 --> 00:37:16.020
He raised me the way he
wanted, which helped me a lot.

00:37:16.380 --> 00:37:21.180
In general, the cooperation and everything
I went through with him was phenomenal.

00:37:22.380 --> 00:37:29.460
When I started playing,
I think  it was the third month

00:37:30.020 --> 00:37:36.060
or the end of the second,
there was this fatal fall

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:39.940
in the game against
Sevilla at the Calderon.

00:37:41.420 --> 00:37:47.420
I tore my posterior cruciate ligament
practically in the 30th second of the game.

00:37:48.340 --> 00:37:51.460
We started from the center,
the long pass went to me.

00:37:51.740 --> 00:37:56.260
I was young, overjoyed
because I was playing,

00:37:56.500 --> 00:38:01.380
in a burst of energy...
The fans were there too.

00:38:01.620 --> 00:38:11.140
I had a duel where my posterior
cruciate ligament got injured.

00:38:12.940 --> 00:38:15.212
I tried to get up,
but my leg remained blocked

00:38:15.301 --> 00:38:17.341
and I couldn't even move.

00:38:18.820 --> 00:38:24.220
At that moment, at the age of 25,
I experienced... -Serious injury.

00:38:24.540 --> 00:38:30.380
Yes. I had to face something
that was completely foreign to me.

00:38:30.580 --> 00:38:33.340
How did you feel those first few days?

00:38:34.220 --> 00:38:38.500
The first information is that
you will not play for 8 months.

00:38:39.300 --> 00:38:43.940
No. In the first days,
I went for a check-up.

00:38:44.180 --> 00:38:48.100
I knew something was wrong
and that the knee was locked.

00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:52.420
When I pull it aside, it goes back.
I realized something was wrong.

00:38:53.580 --> 00:38:57.099
I was afraid of a cruciate
ligament injury because

00:38:57.352 --> 00:39:01.411
I had seen many such injuries
during my career up to that point.

00:39:02.460 --> 00:39:03.638
I kept saying:

00:39:03.748 --> 00:39:06.068
"God, if only it wasn't
the cruciate ligaments.

00:39:06.207 --> 00:39:08.167
If only it wasn't the anterior
cruciate ligament."

00:39:08.299 --> 00:39:10.259
And it was much worse than that.
-Yes, much worse.

00:39:10.493 --> 00:39:14.133
At the first examination,
they told me that it was

00:39:15.180 --> 00:39:18.729
the anterior cruciate ligaments
and sent me home.  I went home.

00:39:19.660 --> 00:39:25.860
Then I called Dr. Nemec
and told him: "Doctor, I'm fine.

00:39:26.460 --> 00:39:29.580
I can squat, I'm fine."

00:39:32.881 --> 00:39:36.660
And he says to me: "Does
it hurt when you take a step?

00:39:37.700 --> 00:39:40.620
Something happened
inside, but I can squat.

00:39:40.860 --> 00:39:43.700
All night I thought about
what was wrong with me.

00:39:44.220 --> 00:39:47.180
Because they said it was
the anterior cruciate ligament

00:39:47.420 --> 00:39:49.900
and I was in shock.

00:39:52.300 --> 00:39:54.540
The next afternoon,
when I went for an examination,

00:39:54.727 --> 00:39:57.460
they told me that it was indeed
a rupture of the

00:39:57.696 --> 00:39:59.936
posterior cruciate ligament.

00:40:02.014 --> 00:40:05.163
When I sighed, they asked me
what was wrong with me?

00:40:05.920 --> 00:40:09.590
Because they said a partial rupture
of the posterior cruciate ligament

00:40:09.786 --> 00:40:11.999
is not a terrible injury.
- No surgery needed, ideally.

00:40:12.288 --> 00:40:15.575
"It's not that dangerous, players
can play with it without problems."

00:40:15.818 --> 00:40:21.215
I said, "Great, great."
I took a break for 3 or 4 months.

00:40:22.749 --> 00:40:27.063
I think the break lasted 3 months.
I went to therapy.

00:40:28.392 --> 00:40:31.063
You were in Madrid the whole time?
-That's right.

00:40:31.235 --> 00:40:35.127
Then I went to Zadar
with my godfather.

00:40:35.376 --> 00:40:40.034
Marko Damjanović is actually
my child's godfather.

00:40:40.291 --> 00:40:44.924
A man who has been
my friend for six years.

00:40:45.447 --> 00:40:50.350
We met when my agony began.
So we just enjoyed ourselves.

00:40:50.604 --> 00:40:53.764
In six years you have
managed to make friends.

00:40:54.980 --> 00:40:58.860
Then I started working
with him in Zadar.

00:40:59.180 --> 00:41:02.820
When we met, I told him about
the problem I had, because

00:41:03.100 --> 00:41:08.740
I noticed that I couldn't sprint,
that my knee was blocked.

00:41:09.380 --> 00:41:12.813
At the end of that season
in which I was injured,

00:41:12.969 --> 00:41:15.118
Diego Simeone told me:

00:41:15.305 --> 00:41:18.378
"I want you to be healthy at the
beginning of the next season.

00:41:18.516 --> 00:41:23.429
So, you can only guess how it
was presented to him, but also to me.

00:41:25.071 --> 00:41:29.698
It meant: "I want you
healthy for the preparations.

00:41:30.050 --> 00:41:33.514
I don't have a partial,
but a complete rupture

00:41:34.964 --> 00:41:40.804
of the posterior cruciate
ligament, my knee drops out.

00:41:41.540 --> 00:41:44.252
In the case of anterior
cruciate ligament injury,

00:41:44.386 --> 00:41:46.486
the arch falls forward,
and in the case of

00:41:46.671 --> 00:41:48.551
a posterior cruciate ligament injury,
it falls backwards.

00:41:48.692 --> 00:41:51.431
I could practically... -How is it
possible that this has not been

00:41:51.619 --> 00:41:55.017
diagnosed in a club
like Atletico Madrid?

00:41:55.280 --> 00:41:58.900
No, I don't want to attribute it
to the doctors.

00:41:59.740 --> 00:42:05.788
I think that at that moment,
the fault was only mine,

00:42:06.700 --> 00:42:13.260
because from my early youth I was
used to deal with all the problems

00:42:13.940 --> 00:42:18.740
that I come across. I beat it.
That's how I experienced this too.

00:42:18.980 --> 00:42:22.100
This is a partial rupture, I can beat
it, because it's nothing so terrible.

00:42:22.380 --> 00:42:27.220
However, when I started
working with Marko that summer

00:42:27.500 --> 00:42:29.900
I realized I had
a serious problem.

00:42:30.220 --> 00:42:34.460
I don't have the same step anymore,
I don'thave the same speed,

00:42:34.740 --> 00:42:37.500
I struggled. During the preparations,
I saw them looking at me

00:42:37.740 --> 00:42:41.020
and quietly whispering:
"He's still hurting."

00:42:42.100 --> 00:42:47.500
That year,and that's
the current season...

00:42:47.780 --> 00:42:51.380
That year you won the UEFA Cup.

00:42:51.660 --> 00:42:55.220
We won the UEFA Cup
and the World Cup is coming.

00:42:55.500 --> 00:43:01.780
I am aware of that at the beginning
of the season. -You have to be ready.

00:43:02.780 --> 00:43:08.580
Not knowing what problem I have,
I continue to play for a year.

00:43:08.696 --> 00:43:11.792
At first it was a disaster,
I felt abnormal pains,

00:43:11.927 --> 00:43:14.410
in the back of the knee.

00:43:14.949 --> 00:43:18.087
However, no one told me at
the time: "Šime, a complete rupture

00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:21.022
of the posterior cruciate
ligament requires surgery.

00:43:21.192 --> 00:43:23.169
If you don't, your cartilage
will get damaged,

00:43:23.340 --> 00:43:25.243
and when it does, it's done.

00:43:25.388 --> 00:43:27.490
Some hard words were spoken
in some moments

00:43:27.685 --> 00:43:29.805
when it comes to your illness.

00:43:35.580 --> 00:43:42.780
Some media even
mentioned amputation.

00:43:43.660 --> 00:43:51.460
Everything has reached
that level. -Yes.

00:43:52.660 --> 00:43:55.060
They said not only that
you can't play,

00:43:55.240 --> 00:43:58.176
but you can't even walk normally
and that you could stay

00:43:58.321 --> 00:44:00.081
without a part of his body.

00:44:00.820 --> 00:44:04.580
Yes, it was, but those
comments came later.

00:44:04.820 --> 00:44:10.180
The World Cup went as it went.

00:44:11.780 --> 00:44:14.460
That's a separate topic.
We'll leave that for last.

00:44:14.622 --> 00:44:17.102
I wouldn't change anything
and if the same thing

00:44:17.218 --> 00:44:19.578
happened again,
I would do it all over again.

00:44:21.740 --> 00:44:24.700
After the World Cup,
I'm going to Inter.

00:44:26.260 --> 00:44:31.660
It is again the realization
of a dream that I started in Italy.

00:44:31.861 --> 00:44:33.981
I was given the opportunity
to realize it

00:44:34.105 --> 00:44:36.146
and I accepted it wholeheartedly.

00:44:39.220 --> 00:44:44.500
And in the first month
of that year, as an Inter player,

00:44:44.740 --> 00:44:47.620
I decided for the surgery.

00:44:48.500 --> 00:44:51.740
I felt the same way when
I stopped playing football

00:44:51.879 --> 00:44:53.995
and when I went for surgery.

00:44:54.660 --> 00:44:58.018
So it was purely your decision,
without any pressure?

00:44:58.210 --> 00:45:00.330
You simply said:
"I can't do it anymore."

00:45:00.619 --> 00:45:04.370
I couldn't take it anymore,
it didn't make sense.

00:45:04.580 --> 00:45:06.700
Everything I did was torture.

00:45:06.980 --> 00:45:09.820
It wasn't the same player anymore,
it wasn't the same pace,

00:45:09.935 --> 00:45:11.800
it wasn't the same power.

00:45:12.129 --> 00:45:16.621
My psychological and mental
preparations for match

00:45:16.896 --> 00:45:20.136
with such a knee
made me weaker than others,

00:45:20.430 --> 00:45:23.270
as much as I thought
I could handle it.

00:45:23.663 --> 00:45:27.925
You can't just play
a year without an ACL.

00:45:28.593 --> 00:45:34.963
The scans showed that
the cartilage had been consumed

00:45:36.011 --> 00:45:41.223
to such an extent that it
practically almost exploded.

00:45:45.573 --> 00:45:48.573
I made the decision
to have surgery

00:45:48.900 --> 00:45:50.980
after which the recovery
lasted nine months.

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:54.780
After the surgery I came back
and continued to play.

00:45:55.060 --> 00:45:58.340
After that, before each match,
I had to have an injection,

00:45:59.020 --> 00:46:01.460
because I was experiencing
unbelievable pain.

00:46:01.685 --> 00:46:05.881
During the operation they put in,
as they call it, a "hook".

00:46:06.101 --> 00:46:09.288
It is an internal seam that they
take out after a certain time.

00:46:09.596 --> 00:46:14.000
I'm back and playing, but nothing
is the same as it was.

00:46:15.148 --> 00:46:18.940
Mobility is reduced
after that operation.

00:46:19.140 --> 00:46:22.420
The step is not the same, but I'm back.
I looked good in some games.

00:46:23.160 --> 00:46:29.266
I came back full of motivation,
desire and will, but corona is coming.

00:46:31.020 --> 00:46:35.620
That got you too.
-After the corona, I'm coming back.

00:46:36.740 --> 00:46:45.500
And during those mini-preparations,
I hurt my calf.

00:46:47.580 --> 00:46:51.500
And then they say to me: "Great
Šime, when the leg is already

00:46:51.820 --> 00:46:56.780
injured, let's take advantage of
the situation and take out the "hook".

00:47:01.300 --> 00:47:06.420
They recommend me an Argentine
doctor in Madrid.

00:47:06.686 --> 00:47:10.721
Although I had the feeling that it was
better to go to the doctor in Belgium,

00:47:10.870 --> 00:47:13.030
who operated on me the first time.

00:47:13.820 --> 00:47:16.700
I don't want to create tension,
I'm back.

00:47:16.940 --> 00:47:23.140
There were tensions before,
during the period,

00:47:23.780 --> 00:47:28.460
when I was in Atletico Madrid.
I didn't want to spite myself.

00:47:28.740 --> 00:47:34.380
I'll let them decide.
And I will accept their decision.

00:47:37.580 --> 00:47:43.060
They operated on me, removed
the hook and I returned home.

00:47:43.460 --> 00:47:47.300
It was supposed to be a routine
operation, nothing special.

00:47:48.420 --> 00:47:51.100
At home I have fever seven days.

00:47:51.340 --> 00:47:55.780
When they took off the patch.
The inside of my knee is not healing,

00:47:56.060 --> 00:48:00.380
there was a hole
and I could see the bone.

00:48:01.740 --> 00:48:08.140
They are taking me back
to the doctor who operated on me.

00:48:09.140 --> 00:48:11.300
I tell the doctor that
something is wrong.

00:48:11.580 --> 00:48:15.460
I have a fever, I can't
sleep because of great pain.

00:48:15.597 --> 00:48:17.877
I toss and turn on the bed at night.

00:48:18.017 --> 00:48:21.177
When I bend my knee,
the blood goes into my sock.

00:48:21.298 --> 00:48:22.858
Something is wrong.

00:48:23.300 --> 00:48:28.260
He says: "Šime, that skin..."
And he sews up again.

00:48:29.340 --> 00:48:33.180
I'm already angry and annoyed.
I can see something is wrong.

00:48:33.420 --> 00:48:37.420
I get home, pull my leg. I want
to see if it will happen again?

00:48:37.620 --> 00:48:42.220
It pops again and the blood
is in the sock.

00:48:43.580 --> 00:48:48.060
I urgently call the doctor and tell
him that something is happening.

00:48:48.260 --> 00:48:52.660
I have a hole in my knee and
blood is flowing continuously.

00:48:53.140 --> 00:48:56.420
My knee has a strange color
and it's not okay.

00:48:56.820 --> 00:49:02.100
They took me to the same doctor again.
He watches carefully and does this...

00:49:02.300 --> 00:49:07.500
I say to him: "Tell me, doctor?"
"You have to have surgery," he says.

00:49:07.740 --> 00:49:10.380
Two operations in ten days.
And an emergency operation.

00:49:10.620 --> 00:49:15.580
I ask him what it is and he quietly
tells that it is an infection.

00:49:16.620 --> 00:49:20.220
I said in amazement:
"What an infection, doctor?"

00:49:20.460 --> 00:49:25.300
I come here for seven days.
I tell you something is wrong.

00:49:25.500 --> 00:49:29.020
You stitch me up three times.

00:49:30.020 --> 00:49:33.740
I've been here for seven days,
I could have lost my leg.

00:49:34.020 --> 00:49:37.220
An emergency operation has been did
lest something serious happens.

00:49:37.374 --> 00:49:39.494
The infection has spread quite a bit.

00:49:39.711 --> 00:49:42.951
Through the operated cartilage
and everything you else.

00:49:43.142 --> 00:49:45.582
They reacted at the last moment.

00:49:46.620 --> 00:49:54.300
After that operation I lost 8-9 kg.
I was on morphine.

00:49:55.220 --> 00:50:01.100
After that, I get into a situation
like when I had the first operation.

00:50:03.180 --> 00:50:10.861
All over again? -That's right. I'm
losing 9 kg, morphine, antibiotics.

00:50:16.700 --> 00:50:20.540
The biggest damage happened
during that infection.

00:50:20.780 --> 00:50:24.380
The first operation
didn't make sense.

00:50:24.620 --> 00:50:27.660
When the infection started,
everything went wrong.

00:50:27.860 --> 00:50:30.780
In addition to that infection,
I also had a fourth operation.

00:50:31.020 --> 00:50:34.380
There were adhesions
and other complications...

00:50:36.180 --> 00:50:41.740
A sad story indeed.
-Honestly, it's not for me.

00:50:42.476 --> 00:50:46.218
Now, from this perspective,
the UEFA Cup,

00:50:46.380 --> 00:50:49.515
with the national team
the icing on the career,

00:50:49.860 --> 00:50:54.054
and then comes the cooling.
-It's not like that.

00:50:55.022 --> 00:51:00.244
How old were you then? 25-26?
-Well, 25.

00:51:01.220 --> 00:51:05.540
Somewhere around the 28th,
everything unfolds.

00:51:05.940 --> 00:51:10.380
For everything positive and negative,
the peak is in those years.

00:51:10.660 --> 00:51:15.740
In my best years,
I lived through it all.

00:51:16.020 --> 00:51:23.460
Yes, all those stresses... And then
your life hangs in the balance?

00:51:23.740 --> 00:51:27.020
I don't regret a single day,
nor for the surgeries,

00:51:27.260 --> 00:51:31.060
nor for the antibiotics, really.
I fought everything to the end.

00:51:32.820 --> 00:51:36.060
Did you fight as hard as you could?
-I did my best.

00:51:36.500 --> 00:51:40.420
Looking back, maybe I should have
stopped playing football earlier,

00:51:40.580 --> 00:51:42.340
considering everything.

00:51:42.540 --> 00:51:46.660
Let's talk about the crown
of your career.

00:51:50.329 --> 00:51:56.660
Describe 2018 for me,
from the medal onward.

00:51:58.980 --> 00:52:05.580
Forget everything before. I want to hear
about your welcome in Zagreb and Zadar.

00:52:06.580 --> 00:52:08.820
Welcome of hope.

00:52:10.660 --> 00:52:15.485
What was it like to live in Croatia
during those days and months? -Unreal.

00:52:16.380 --> 00:52:19.980
I have to admit that I watched
every game. It was madness.

00:52:20.260 --> 00:52:23.260
When I first looked
from this perspective,

00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:29.860
the whole country was on its feet.
Everyone lived for those moments.

00:52:30.100 --> 00:52:34.300
I can't imagine how it was for you.
I guess when you're inside,

00:52:34.540 --> 00:52:37.580
you don't have a sense
of what  it's like outside.

00:52:37.780 --> 00:52:39.740
But how was it when you arrived?

00:52:40.020 --> 00:52:48.140
I remember the moment when
Dario Srna, the eternal captain,

00:52:48.820 --> 00:52:52.140
who did so much for
the Croatian national team,

00:52:52.740 --> 00:52:56.540
and the man with whom I shared
the same dressing room for a long time,

00:52:56.780 --> 00:53:00.700
came to our hotel as a guest and
told us that we were not normal.

00:53:00.900 --> 00:53:07.020
That we didn't know what was happening in
Croatia and what kind of euphoria it was.

00:53:07.660 --> 00:53:12.900
That was the first time I realized...
-Something clicked in your head.

00:53:13.100 --> 00:53:16.140
The information came to me because
we were isolated from everything.

00:53:16.380 --> 00:53:20.660
Messages were coming in,
but we weren't focused on that.

00:53:22.500 --> 00:53:25.220
And we didn't even have time.

00:53:26.100 --> 00:53:28.860
We needed to be concentrated
on what was coming.

00:53:29.060 --> 00:53:33.260
Our primary task was
to achieve the best possible result.

00:53:34.100 --> 00:53:38.020
Everything that happened, happened.
It's over, and I'm coming back.

00:53:38.660 --> 00:53:52.860
I don't know... that arrival in Zagreb.
Those fighet jets that flew by us.

00:53:57.620 --> 00:54:00.300
It's hard to be aware of all that.

00:54:00.580 --> 00:54:07.900
That euphoria, laughter,
and energy discharge.

00:54:08.380 --> 00:54:13.260
It's just... -You still can't find
the right words?

00:54:13.460 --> 00:54:16.660
And after five years,
the impressions are still strong.

00:54:16.940 --> 00:54:19.380
It cannot be described.

00:54:19.620 --> 00:54:24.780
It's something that happens
once in your life.

00:54:24.980 --> 00:54:27.300
You live through that.

00:54:27.660 --> 00:54:34.380
And carry it with you when
your mission in this world is finished.

00:54:35.180 --> 00:54:39.500
It's hard to describe this with words,
that emotion, which happened

00:54:39.700 --> 00:54:44.540
minute by minute,
in my body and in my head.

00:54:46.180 --> 00:54:49.940
As you absorbed all that energy,
you thought you were on top?

00:54:50.180 --> 00:54:55.711
Is it possible that so much
love was coming in?

00:54:55.969 --> 00:54:59.180
You feel like you're going
to explode from happiness.

00:54:59.380 --> 00:55:01.420
You don't know what to do.

00:55:01.660 --> 00:55:09.467
You want to entertain those people.
You want to animate them; I don't know.

00:55:11.060 --> 00:55:22.260
Simply, you feel that strong love
and energy...

00:55:23.060 --> 00:55:28.079
It is really had to get
acknowledged, especially in Croatia.

00:55:28.232 --> 00:55:31.931
You know how difficult it is
with the national team?

00:55:33.220 --> 00:55:35.460
And what is our mentality?

00:55:35.700 --> 00:55:38.340
What is that amount of love for
the Croatian national team?

00:55:38.540 --> 00:55:43.371
The ladder was raised in 1998.
We lived with that.

00:55:43.463 --> 00:55:45.783
And generations before us.

00:55:46.660 --> 00:55:51.100
God looked at us, probably,
we deserved it in some way.

00:55:51.300 --> 00:55:55.780
He knows it best.
-Of course. Šime, thank you.

00:55:56.140 --> 00:55:58.780
The pleasure is mine.
-It's mine, too.

00:55:59.060 --> 00:56:02.900
I wish you that never again
you get injured.

00:56:03.100 --> 00:56:06.680
Not now, only in the morning.
-Good luck! -Thank you.

